{
  "texts": [
    "The Levin-Wen Hamiltonian has a unique frustration free ground state which we denote by ω 1.",
    "This frustration free ground state is pure.We present an independent proof at the end of section 5.2 below.",
    "We let (π 1, H, Ω) be the GNS triple of ω 1.",
    "Since ω 1 is pure, the vacuum representation π 1 is irreducible.",
    "Classification of irreducible anyon sectorsThe cone with apex at a ∈ R 2, axis v ∈ R 2 of unit length, and opening angle θ ∈ (0, 2π) is the open subset of R 2 given by Λ a,v,θ:= {x ∈ R 2: (x -a) • v > ∥x -a∥ cos(θ/2)}.Any subset Λ ⊂ R 2 of this form will be called a cone."
  ]
}